  "texts": [
    "As mentioned above, dim B ≤ 1 yields locally homogeneous expanding solitons.",
    "We are left with the case dim B = dim N = 2.",
    "Here, Corollary D and Hitchin's explicit description of the moduli space of SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundles [Hit87, §10] yield a complete description of 4D affine expanding solitons, which we detail in Section 5.",
    "In particular, we obtain the following: Corollary E. Let B 2 be a closed surface of genus g ≥ 3.",
    "Then, there exists a family, depending on 10g -14 = 4(g -2)+6(g -1) real parameters, of affine expanding Ricci solitons with constant scalar curvature on twisted principal bundles M 4 = B × ρ R 2 over B, none of which is gradient or locally homogeneous.For genus g = 2 we still get a 6 = 6(g -1)-dimensional family of examples, reflecting the different choices of conformal structures on B."
